        "old_string": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Serializer\",\n      \"type\": \"interface\",\n      \"role\": \"defines\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Deserializer\",\n      \"type\": \"interface\",\n      \"role\": \"defines\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"DeserializationSchema\",\n      \"type\": \"interface\",\n      \"role\": \"defines\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The serialization boundary between Kafka and Flink is defined by three key interfaces:\\n\\n**Kafka Side (org.apache.kafka):**\\n1. `Serializer<T>` interface (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java) - Converts objects to bytes for Kafka topics. It provides the core method `byte[] serialize(String topic, T data)` and an overloaded version with Headers support. The interface extends Closeable for proper resource management.\\n\\n2. `Deserializer<T>` interface (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java) - Converts bytes from Kafka topics back into objects. It provides the core method `T deserialize(String topic, byte[] data)` and overloaded versions supporting Headers and ByteBuffer inputs.\\n\\n**Flink Side (org.apache.flink):**\\n3. `DeserializationSchema<T>` interface (github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java) - Flink's abstraction for converting byte messages from data sources (like Kafka) into Java/Scala objects. It provides `T deserialize(byte[] message)` and overloaded versions with Collector support for multiple records. Notably, this interface is designed to be source-agnostic and extends ResultTypeQueryable to provide type information.\\n\\n**The Boundary:**\\nThe key difference is that Kafka's Deserializer is topic-aware (takes topic name as parameter), while Flink's DeserializationSchema is topic-agnostic and designed to work with any data source. Flink's KafkaSource connector (found in org.apache.flink.connector.kafka.source package) bridges these by wrapping Kafka's Deserializer through KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema, which adapts Kafka's topic-aware deserialization to Flink's DeserializationSchema interface.\"\n}",
        "new_string": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-examples/flink-examples-streaming/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/examples/statemachine/kafka/EventDeSerializationSchema.java\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Serializer\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489\",\n      \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Deserializer\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"DeserializationSchema\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-examples/flink-examples-streaming/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/examples/statemachine/kafka/EventDeSerializationSchema.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"EventDeSerializationSchema\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc\",\n      \"path\": \"flink-examples/flink-examples-streaming/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/examples/statemachine/StateMachineExample.java\",\n      \"symbol\": \"KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema.valueOnly\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The serialization boundary between Kafka and Flink is defined by these key interfaces and classes:\\n\\n**Kafka Interfaces (org.apache.kafka.common.serialization):**\\n1. `Serializer<T>` (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Serializer.java) - Interface defining how objects are converted to bytes for Kafka. Core method: `byte[] serialize(String topic, T data)`.\\n\\n2. `Deserializer<T>` (github.com/sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/serialization/Deserializer.java) - Interface defining how bytes are converted back to objects. Core method: `T deserialize(String topic, byte[] data)`.\\n\\n**Flink Abstraction (org.apache.flink.api.common.serialization):**\\n3. `DeserializationSchema<T>` (github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-core/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/api/common/serialization/DeserializationSchema.java) - Flink's source-agnostic abstraction for deserialization. Core method: `T deserialize(byte[] message)`. This interface is designed to work with any data source (Kafka, files, sockets, etc.) and provides type information through ResultTypeQueryable.\\n\\n**Bridge/Wrapper Implementation:**\\n4. `EventDeSerializationSchema` (github.com/sg-evals/flink--0cc95fcc/flink-examples/flink-examples-streaming/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/examples/statemachine/kafka/EventDeSerializationSchema.java) - A concrete implementation that shows how to wrap Kafka deserialization logic. It implements both DeserializationSchema<Event> and SerializationSchema<Event>.\\n\\n**Key Difference at the Boundary:**\\nKafka's Deserializer is topic-aware (requires topic name as a parameter), while Flink's DeserializationSchema is topic-agnostic and designed to work with multiple data sources. Flink's KafkaSource connector bridges this gap using `KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema.valueOnly()`, which adapts Kafka-specific deserialization to Flink's DeserializationSchema interface. This allows Flink to treat Kafka the same way it treats other sources (files, sockets, etc.), providing a unified abstraction layer for data deserialization.\"\n}",
